Port Elizabeth Dutywa police in the Eastern Cape are investigating a case of culpable homicide following a fatal accident that left a family of four dead. Police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha, said the accident between a truck and a Sedan occurred along the N2 between Dutywa and Butterworth on Wednesday evening. Manatha said the family of four travelling in the Sedan died instantly. &quot;All of them died instantly at the accident scene. The father was 53, mother 42 and their two children aged five and 15.&quot; The truck driver and a passenger were seriously injured and rushed to Butterworth hospital. African News Agency